		{
			dependencies: ["34D049FD2BF84E84"]
			description: [
				"The most straightforwad way to generate energy by burning solid fuel. There three types of solid fuel generators you can make now."
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&lHeat Generator&r is hybrid gen that easier to make. It can convert solid fuels or even lava into internal fuel capacity to generate some amount of energy in quick succession, but it's fuel efficiency left much to be desired."
				""
				"One of hiden talants of HG is to convert thermal heat of adjacent lava sources into very small amount of energy per seconds. "
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&lCoal Generator&r is fuel efficient and will more slowly burn out fuel unlike it's relatives, but its energy output is rather slow. In theory it can generate more energy in the long run while your network is in congestion. "
				""
				"It will stop burning fuel and even freeze burning timer if it can't output."
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&lStirling Dynamo&r optimal in generating a moderate amount of energy with average fuel consumption. It's output based on local demand: it will output less energy if network have abundance of it, but will still burn fuel. "
				""
				"If no fuel is provided and energy don't go anywhere, dynamo will loose stored amount very slowly overtime. "
			]
